"MOON GARDEN","3","Ky Son, Xuan Son, Hanoi","(+84) 4. 33261156","As a small village, Moon Garden homestay has the traditional ancient houses,  house on stilt, and a Moon Garden hall. Ancient houses are Mango house,  Pomelo house  Frangipani house in  traditional style with 3 parts of living room and two bedrooms, and a smaller house with only one bedroom: Guava house. Why the houses are calling ancient house? Because tourists can find the traditional architecture features here. The roof  tile is Vietnam's traditional tile called shoe peak tile or dragon scale tile. The doors and almost the furniture are made from wood. The houses are decorated by distiches, all the furniture as tables, ottomans, beds are decorated by carving traditional pattern: lotus, peach blossom, phoenix and dragon. The windows have the circle shape that symbolize for conception of Yin and Yang. Especially, the Frangipani house has the Buddha altar with many beautiful Buddha statues: Bodhisattva statues, Maitreya statuse... In front of the house is a large yard where children can play traditional games. The yard has areca and betel trees that involve to a folktale in Vietnam. Moon Garden homestay also has a large garden with many kind of fruits and flowers as pomelo, mango, logan and many frangipani.","*** CANCELLATION POLICY ***: By 30 days: no charge. 15 - 30 days: 10%, 10 - 15 days: 20%, 5 - 10 days: 30%. Within 48 hrs: 50%. No show: 100%.
